National Geographic Travel
It’s a big world. Explore it through the lens of our photographers.
on.natgeo.com/travel

posts.description: Photo by @juancristobalcobo / An unusual view of dawn at Alto de Ventanas in northern Antioquia, Colombia. This particular spot in the Colombian central Andes is almost always covered by heavy fog, but on this morning I could see all the way to the Cauca River Basin. #caucariver #antioquia #colombia #juancristobalcobo

Photo by Robbie Shone @shonephoto / In 2015 I took part in the first Greenland Caves Project expedition to northeast Greenland. That original expedition, partly supported by the National Geographic Society, was full of adventure. It involved flying as far as we could in a Twin Otter to a tiny airstrip on a sandy spit of land in the middle of nowhere. We inflated a boat and crossed a 20-kilometer-wide (12-mile-wide) lake, then we hiked for three days to get to some small, seemingly insignificant caves near the top of the world. At the time, we didn’t know it would become a recce expedition that would lead to years of research. Professor Gina Moseley, the project leader, collected samples of cave calcite to use to reconstruct records of past climate change. The pilot data proved highly important and resulted in a prestigious FWF Start prize, enabling the research to continue for the next six years. On July 3, 2019, nine people set off on an interdisciplinary expedition back to 80° N.

Photo by Muhammed Muheisen @mmuheisen / How small we appear against monuments of history. In the ancient city of Petra in Jordan, Al Khazneh ("the treasury") is one of many facades carved into the mountains. For more photos and videos from different parts of the world, follow me @mmuheisen and @mmuheisenpublic. #muhammedmuheisen #Jordan #الاردن

Photo by @francescolastrucci / The Sass de Putia stands isolated and imposing at the border of the Puez-Odle Nature Park. With its rugged shape, the mountain is one of the most recognized peaks of the Italian Dolomites. It is renowned for the glorious 360-degree view from the summit. Follow @francescolastrucci for more places, daily life, and stories around the world. #italy #southtyrol #dolomites #landscapephotography

Photo by @sarah_stacke / A horse walks across a field at Gunville Ranch on the Cheyenne River Reservation, a sovereign Lakota nation in the state of South Dakota. Follow @sarah_stacke for more photos and stories celebrating the beauty of the Great Plains. #CheyenneRiverReservation #Lakota #GunvilleRanch #Horse #GreatPlains

Photo by @michaelclarkphoto / This is the view from the torre atop the Serra da Estrela ("star mountain") in central Portugal. The peak, as seen here, is a wide, flat spot that also has a ski area. At an altitude of 1,993 meters (6,539 feet), it was quite cold on the morning of this shoot; it hovered around 2°C (36°F). #portugal #serradaestrela

Photo by @juancristobalcobo / A light drizzle falls on the hills of Santa Rosa de Osos, located in one of the branches of the Cordillera Central, northeast of the department of Antioquia, Colombia. #santarosadeosos #antioquia #colombia #juancristobalcobo

Photo by @michaelclarkphoto / Joe Nodeland kayaks in, around, and through the tiny islands not far from the Johnstone Strait near Vancouver Island in British Columbia, Canada. #seakayaking #canada #johnstonestrait

Photo by Muhammed Muheisen @mmuheisen / On May 1 I flew over the blossoming flower fields in North Holland and other parts of the country while working on a story for National Geographic about the flower season in the Netherlands. For more photos and videos from different parts of the world, follow me @mmuheisen and @mmuheisenpublic. #muhammedmuheisen #Netherlands #Flowers #Tulips

Photos by @francescolastrucci / The town of Cefalù on Sicily’s northern coast has a long history. The Greeks, Phoenicians, Romans, Arabs, and Normans all left traces. The town is dominated by an impressive rock and lapped by turquoise waters. I caught what is probably my favorite beach moment of the day, both for swimming and for photography: when the crowds are gone and the golden light of the sunset glows.
Follow me @francescolastrucci for more places, daily life, and stories around the world. #sicily #italy #dailylife #summer
